exercise_kb('EX_218', 'skull_crusher', 2, ['ez_bar', 'bench'], ['elbow_strain'], [], ['foundation', 'recomposition', 'recomposition', 'hypertrophy_volume', 'strength_block'], ['triceps'], [], ['s_tier'], 'tricep_isolation', false, 'The EZ-bar skullcrusher is a popular exercise targeting the triceps muscles. The EZ-bar is used more often than a straight bar. As for the name, that’s worst-case scenario. The bar should actually come down behind the head. It is usually performed for moderate to high reps as part of an upper body or arms-focused workout. No need to chase a 1RM on this move!', 'K3mFeNz4e3w').
